Introduction

Kisu is a South Korean singer-songwriter and former member of the boy group 24K and their subunit 4K. As a solo artist, he went by the name Soo and debuted on December 22, 2017, with his first studio album, Sweet Lie.

Kisu debuted as a member of unit 4K on June 12, 2012, with the release of their mini album Rocking Girl. He then debuted in the group 24K on September 6, 2012, with their mini album Hurry Up. He made his solo debut on December 22, 2017, under the stage name Soo with his album Sweet Lie. On February 1, 2020, Kisu announced his departure from 24K.

He enlisted in the military on May 11, 2018, and was discharged in 2020.
